In large saucepan cook pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile, in large skillet heat olive oil over medium heat until hot. Add onion, garlic and red pepper flakes; cook and stir 4 minutes or until onions are softened. Add bell peppers, shrimp and oregano; cook and stir 10 minutes or until peppers are tender and shrimp are pink. Stir in olives; remove from heat. Toss sauce with hot cooked noodles; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Season with salt and pepper if desired.